tourBios.curYearHigh: In PGA TOUR rookie season managed one top-10 finish, despite just three made cuts in 20 starts...Finished T9 at the Sanderson Farms Championship to earn top 10 in just his second career PGA TOUR start. The Mississippi State graduate shot rounds of 70-70-69-69 at the CC of Jackson...Played in seven Web.com Tour Regular Season events, making four cuts with finishes between T27 and T38.
tourBios.carHigh: 2013: Played nine events on Mackenzie Tour - PGA TOUR Canada, making the cut five times...Won the Players Cup with rounds of 65-67-71-68 to finish at 17-under...Finished the season ninth on the Order of Merit...Also won the Long Beach Key Open on the West Florida Golf Tour...Earned victory at the Chicago Open at Cantigny Golf...Missed the cut in his Web.com Tour debut, at the United Leasing Championship.
tourBios.otherCarHigh: Competed in 34 rounds as a freshman at Mississippi State University in 2005-06, recording a team-best scoring average of 73.76...Led State at the Tennessee Tournament of Champions, finishing 12th in his collegiate debut...Finished with five career top-10 finishes in four years at MSU.
tourBios.personal: Attended Larkin High School in the Chicago suburb of Elgin, Ill...Hobbies include hunting, fishing, soccer, tennis and ping pong.

tourBios.carHigh:
2013-14: Ended the season playing in 24 of the Web.com Tour's 25 tournaments, recording one top-10 and four top-25s...Made a double eagle in the opening round of the Chile Classic on the par-5 ninth hole. It was the first albatross in tournament history. Went on to finish T57...Struggled from April through early August, making just two cuts (T14 at the South Georgia Classic and T28 at the United Leasing Championship) over a 12-tournament stretch...Recorded his first top-10 in August, a T2, at the Price Cutter Charity Championship. Fired rounds of 70-66-65-67 (20 under) to finish one shot back of winner Cameron Percy. Matched 67s with Percy on Sunday...Opened the Web.com Tour Finals with a T19 at the Hotel Fitness Championship...After climbing the third-round leaderboard with a 64 at the following week's Chiquita Classic, caught fire at the start of his final round, going 6 under (birdie-birdie-par-eagle-birdie-birdie) on holes 1-6 to get into serious contention. His eagle during the stretch was a hole-in-one. Succumbed to six bogeys over his last 12 holes, which resulted in an even-par round of 72 and a T12 finish. Despite his stumble, the performance put him squarely in contention for a TOUR card via the Finals...Opened the Web.com Tour Finals with a T19 at the Hotel Fitness Championship...Followed it the next week with a T12 at the Chiquita Classic...Missed the cut at the Nationwide Children's Hospital Championship, putting him squarely on the bubble to get one of the 25 available cards heading to the Web.com Tour Championship...A T31 in Ponte Vedra Beach was enough to get the job done as he captured the 49th card.

2013: Played nine events on PGA TOUR Canada, making the cut five times...Won the Players Cup on PGA TOUR Canada with rounds of 65-67-71-68 to finish at 17-under...Finished the season ninth on the Order of Merit...Also won the Long Beach Key Open on the West Florida Golf Tour...Earned victory at the Chicago Open at Cantigny Golf...Missed the cut in his Web.com Tour debut, at the United Leasing Championship.
